{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"Classify every LLM failure into the closed resolution-disposition enum paired with a SANITIZED verbatim diagnostic, replacing the opaque `except Exception -> LLMUnavailableError` collapse — without breaking existing `LLMUnavailableError` consumers.\n\n## Why\n`src/rebar/llm/runner.py:349-361` flattens auth, 429, 529, timeout, and content-filter into one `LLMUnavailableError` — no caller can tell \"retry\" from \"buy quota\" from \"fix config\" from \"the agent is looping.\" Downstream gates, exit codes, messaging, and telemetry need a typed disposition plus the raw truth for troubleshooting. But existing code already catches `LLMUnavailableError` and depends on its behavior, and a raw provider error body can carry secrets — both must be handled.\n\n## What\nIntroduce `classify_llm_failure(exc, ctx) -> LLMOutcome{resolution_class, diagnostic, retryable}` at the single runner except-seam. Map exception -> one of the 8 closed classes; carry a verbatim `diagnostic` (exception type, status_code, provider body error-code, finish_reason, Retry-After, attempts, trace_id, model, provider). The `resolution_class` on the outcome is the SIGNAL the CLI/gate later maps to an exit code (see story 2eca) — it must be carried on the verdict/coverage, not recomputed.\n- **Back-compat:** the new typed errors subclass `LLMUnavailableError` so every existing `except LLMUnavailableError` site still catches; audit and enumerate those consumers (grep `LLMUnavailableError`) and pin their behavior with tests.\n- **Diagnostic sanitization contract (concrete mechanism, not just an ADR):** the diagnostic is built from an ALLOWLIST of fields (exception type, status_code, provider error `code`/`type`, finish_reason, Retry-After, attempts, trace_id, model, provider) — the raw provider body is NEVER dumped wholesale. Any free-text message that IS captured passes through a redactor that masks: `Authorization`/`x-api-key`/`api-key`/`cookie` header values, bearer tokens, and key-shaped tokens (`sk-…`, `sk-ant-…`, and generic long base64/hex secrets), plus email addresses. The redactor is a single pure function with a table of patterns, unit-tested against a body carrying a planted secret. This story AUTHORS the allowlist + redactor mechanism; the corresponding ADR is RECORDED by story 2eca (the sole ADR/docs owner) — not co-owned here.\n\n### Exception → resolution_class mapping (the closed vocabulary)\n| Signal | resolution_class | retryable |\n|---|---|---|\n| `ModelHTTPError` 429 with body code rate/`overloaded` ; 529 ; 500/502/503/504 | WAIT_AND_RETRY | yes |\n| `httpx.ConnectError`/`ConnectTimeout` ; `ModelAPIError` (no status) ; one-off empty/parse blip | RETRY_NOW | yes |\n| 429 with body code `insufficient_quota` ; 402 ; provider hard-quota | INCREASE_PROVIDER_LIMITS | no |\n| 401/403 ; `UserError` (bad model string/config) ; malformed 400 | CHANGE_SETTINGS | no |\n| 400 context-length ; 413 ; `content_filter` finish_reason ; `ContentFilterError` | CHANGE_INPUT | no |\n| validation-retry exhausted ; model can't satisfy schema/tooling ; `FallbackExceptionGroup` | CHANGE_PROVIDER_OR_MODEL | no |\n| `UsageLimitExceeded` (request/tool_calls limit) ; `IncompleteToolCall` ; stuck-loop signature | FIX_AGENT_DESIGN | no |\n| anything unmatched | NEEDS_INVESTIGATION | no |\n\nThe table is the reference the classifier and the RED suite share; `httpx.ReadTimeout` mid-call → WAIT_AND_RETRY. Only the `retryable` column is behaviour-critical; the class is the messaging/telemetry hint.\n- Catch `httpx.*` directly (VERIFIED: they propagate unwrapped). **Unwrap `tenacity.RetryError` first:** the transport's `reraise=True` re-raises the last attempt's original exception on the normal path, but some tenacity paths wrap in a `RetryError` — the classifier must unwrap `RetryError.last_attempt.exception()` to its underlying cause BEFORE matching, or an exhausted-retry `httpx.ReadTimeout`/`ConnectTimeout` would fall through to NEEDS_INVESTIGATION instead of WAIT_AND_RETRY (regression-tested). Discriminate `UnexpectedModelBehavior` subclasses (`ContentFilterError`, `IncompleteToolCall`) rather than bucketing the base class. Total + defensive: an unmatched failure -> NEEDS_INVESTIGATION with full (sanitized) diagnostic; the classifier itself never raises. `UsageLimitExceeded` defaults to FIX_AGENT_DESIGN with step/tool-call counts in the diagnostic to disambiguate loop-vs-legit.\n\n## Scope\n- The closed 8-class enum + the `LLMOutcome` value object + the typed error hierarchy + the sanitization helper.\n- **Public inter-child API boundary:** `LLMOutcome`, the `classify_llm_failure(...)` entry, and the `sanitize_diagnostic(...)` helper live in a single new module `src/rebar/llm/failure.py` (stable path), with documented signatures — story 978d (silent-success routing) imports them from here. Any layout change to this module is a breaking inter-child contract and must be coordinated via story 2eca (the integrator).\n- Provider-body inspection for the terminal-vs-transient 429 split (best-effort, behind the reliable binary retry-or-not core; a misread wastes <= N bounded retries, never a safety issue).\n- NOT in scope: the retry mechanism (story 95a5), the exit-code mapping + gate wiring (story 2eca).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `classify_llm_failure` maps every RED-suite failure class to the correct `resolution_class` + `diagnostic`; unknown -> NEEDS_INVESTIGATION.\n- [ ] Catches `httpx.*` directly; discriminates `UnexpectedModelBehavior` subclasses (`ContentFilterError`, `IncompleteToolCall`).\n- [ ] New typed errors subclass `LLMUnavailableError`; a test enumerates the existing catch/exit-code consumers and asserts their behavior is preserved.\n- [ ] The diagnostic is sanitized (a test injects a fake API key / auth header in a provider body and asserts it is scrubbed from the diagnostic before any sink).\n- [ ] The classifier is total and never raises (property test over arbitrary exceptions).\n- [ ] The corresponding RED-suite cases flip GREEN; `make test`/`make lint`/`make typecheck` green.\n\nFiles: `src/rebar/llm/runner.py`, `src/rebar/llm/errors.py`, a new classifier + sanitizer module under `src/rebar/llm/`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783621106190554001,"uuid":"37c1cf05-d405-4be1-a3aa-2973761bc657"}